abstract: Across America, working-class people — including many of our friends — are dying of despair. And we’re still blaming the wrong people.
snippet: Across America, working-class people — including many of our friends — are dying of despair. And we’re still blaming the wrong people.
lead_paragraph: YAMHILL, Ore. — Chaos reigned daily on the No. 6 school bus, with working-class boys and girls flirting and gossiping and dreaming, brimming with mischief, bravado and optimism. Nick rode it every day in the 1970s with neighbors here in rural Oregon, neighbors like Farlan, Zealan, Rogena, Nathan and Keylan Knapp.

abstract: The company was under intense pressure to adjust its policies. But in this presidential election year, no big changes are planned.
snippet: The company was under intense pressure to adjust its policies. But in this presidential election year, no big changes are planned.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Defying pressure from Congress, Facebook said on Thursday that it would continue to allow political campaigns to use the site to target advertisements to particular slices of the electorate and that it would not police the truthfulness of the messages sent out.

abstract: One policy proposal has defined this Democratic race. It’s time to move on.

lead_paragraph: With strong support among the Democratic Party’s base, “Medicare for all” has emerged as a test of progressive bona fides in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination.

headline_main: Can We Please Stop Fighting About ‘Medicare for All’?

abstract: So far, the president has offered something for both hawks and isolationists. Will that last?

lead_paragraph: Here’s the thing about wartime presidents: They tend to win re-election.

abstract: The online magazine deleted a glowing story about Facebook after questions were raised about whether it was an ad.
snippet: The online magazine deleted a glowing story about Facebook after questions were raised about whether it was an ad.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, Teen Vogue published an article on Facebook’s efforts to safeguard political speech. It had no byline and a glowing tone.

abstract: The designer Rodolphe Parente is a master of mixing unexpected textures and eras, as his latest project proves.
snippet: The designer Rodolphe Parente is a master of mixing unexpected textures and eras, as his latest project proves.
lead_paragraph: The Paris-based architect and designer Rodolphe Parente refuses to subscribe to a signature style. “On each project, we create a different story; we try to have the right tone, to develop the right emotion,” the 39-year-old says of his narrative-driven approach, which is based on interpreting a client’s desires instead of imposing his own mark. For one recent apartment redesign in Monte Carlo, the unique Mediterranean light and the Modernist building itself inspired Parente to work with textured materials that would be enhanced by the changing shadows; by contrast, in 2015 he transformed a Parisian apartment built in 1910 into a spare futuristic pod with concrete walls and glossy red floors, channeling the client’s devotion to Buddhism, modern architecture and David Lynch.

abstract: Awkwafina’s award for her role in “The Farewell” was the film’s only win of the night.
snippet: Awkwafina’s award for her role in “The Farewell” was the film’s only win of the night.
lead_paragraph: Awkwafina on Sunday night became the first Asian-American woman to win a Golden Globe Award for best actress, winning in the musical or comedy category for her role in “The Farewell.”
